The first findings of this originally central Asian species in many countries of central and southern Europe (Italy, Switzerland, France, Germany, Czech Republic, Slovakia, Hungary, Poland) have been reported in many faunistic papers during the last 15 years (

Strejcek
2007

; 
Caldara 2008b
; 

Kratky
and Trnka 2012

; 

Kratky
2013

; 
Germann et al. 2013
; 
Reibnitz 2013
; 

Podlussany
et al. 2017

; 
Wanat and Ruta 2018
; 
Nolte and Haag 2019
). These papers indicate with a high degree of certainty that this species only recently colonized areas where a few years ago it was absent, in contrast to its host plants (
Caldara 2008b
; 
Germann et al. 2013
).
